paragraphs.title: Import Clinical Trials (Rawdata)
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

rawdata = sc.textFile("/clinicaltrials.txt")

header  = rawdata.take(1)

print "\r\n" + "#"*150
print "\r\nTotal Number of Clinical Trials: " + str(rawdata.count())
print "Number of variables in dataset:  " + str(len(header[0].split("|")))
print header
print "\r\n" + "#"*150

paragraphs.title: Format and Structure Dataframe
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

import datetime,re
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import *

def convert_date(date_str):
    try:
        new_date = re.sub(' .+','',str(datetime.datetime.strptime(date_str, '%B %Y')))
    except:
        new_date = ''
    return new_date

df = rawdata.filter(lambda x: x not in header)      \
        .map(lambda x: x.split('|'))                \
        .toDF(header[0].split("|"))

f = udf(convert_date, StringType() )

df2 = df.withColumn('startdate', f(df.start_date)).drop("start_date")

df2.registerTempTable("table_df")
df2.cache()

result.msg: DataFrame[rank: string, status: string, study: string, conditions: string, interventions: string, study_type: string, phase: string, funder_type: string, outcome_measures: string, number_enrolled: string, nct_number: string, startdate: string]

paragraphs.title: Explore Raw Clinical Data
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select * from table_df where study_type="${study_type=Interventional,Interventional|Observational|Expanded Access}" and phase="${phase=Phase 0,Phase 0|Phase 1|Phase 2|Phase 3|Phase 4}" limit 50

                .map(lambda x: x.split('|'))                \

paragraphs.title: Extract N-Grams (Common Phrases)
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

def find_ngrams(list, n):
   return zip(*[list[i:] for i in range(n)])

ngrams =  rawdata.filter(lambda x: x not in header)     \
              .map(lambda x: x.split('|')[2])           \
              .map(lambda x: x.split(' '))              \
              .flatMap(lambda x: find_ngrams(x, 5))     \
              .map(lambda x: (x,1))                     \
              .reduceByKey(lambda x,y: x+y)             \
              .map(lambda x: [x[1],x[0]])               \
              .sortByKey(ascending=False)

for i in ngrams.take(50):
    print i

paragraphs.title: Generate Data-Driven Topics
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

import re
from pyspark.mllib.linalg import SparseVector
from collections import Counter
from pyspark.mllib.clustering import LDA, LDAModel
from pyspark.mllib.linalg import Vectors


number_clusters = 10


rawdata = sc.textFile("/clinicaltrials.txt")
header  = rawdata.take(1)
corpus  = rawdata.filter(lambda x: x not in header)      \
        .map(lambda x: x.split('|')[2])

def cleanup_text(text):
    words = text.split(' ')
    
    stopwords_core = ['a', u'about', u'above', u'after', u'again', u'against', u'ain', u'all', u'am', u'an', u'and', u'any', u'are', u'aren', u'as', u'at', u'be', u'because', u'been', u'before', u'being', u'below', u'between', u'both', u'but', u'by', u'can', 'come', u'could', u'd', u'did', u'didn', u'do', u'does', u'doesn', u'doing', u'don', u'down', u'during', u'each', u'few', u'for', u'from', u'further', u'had', u'hadn', u'has', u'hasn', u'have', u'haven', u'having', u'he', u'her', u'here', u'hers', u'herself', u'him', u'himself', u'his', u'how', u'i', u'if', u'in', u'into', u'is', u'isn', u'it', u'its', u'itself', u'just', u'll', u'm', u'ma', u'me', u'mightn', u'more', u'most', u'mustn', u'my', u'myself', u'needn', u'no', u'nor', u'not', u'now', u'o', u'of', u'off', u'on', u'once', u'only', u'or', u'other', u'our', u'ours', u'ourselves', u'out', u'over', u'own', u're', u's', 'said', u'same', u'shan', u'she', u'should', u'shouldn', u'so', u'some', u'such', u't', u'than', u'that', u'the', u'their', u'theirs', u'them', u'themselves', u'then', u'there', u'these', u'they', u'this', u'those', u'through', u'to', u'too', u'under', u'until', u'up', u've', u'very', u'was', u'wasn', u'we', u'were', u'weren', u'what', u'when', u'where', u'which', u'while', u'who', u'whom', u'why', u'will', u'with', u'won', u'would', u'y', u'you', u'your', u'yours', u'yourself', u'yourselves']
    
    stopwords_custom = ['study','subjects','patients','patient','treating','phase']
    stopwords = stopwords_core + stopwords_custom
    stopwords = [word.lower() for word in stopwords]    
    
    text_out = [word.lower() for word in words if len(word)>2 and word.lower() not in stopwords]
    text_out = [re.sub('[^a-zA-Z0-9]','',word) for word in text_out]
    
    return text_out

tokenized_corpus = corpus.map(cleanup_text).cache()

'''
tokenized_corpus = corpus                   \
    .map(lambda raw_text: raw_text.split()) \
    .cache()
'''

local_vocab_map = tokenized_corpus  \
    .flatMap(lambda token: token)   \
    .distinct()                     \
    .zipWithIndex()

local_vocab_map1 = local_vocab_map.collectAsMap()
vocab_map_vk = sc.broadcast(local_vocab_map1)
vocab_size = sc.broadcast(len(local_vocab_map1))

local_vocab_map2 = local_vocab_map.map(lambda x: (x[1],x[0])).collectAsMap()
vocab_map_kv = sc.broadcast(local_vocab_map2)

term_document_matix = tokenized_corpus  \
    .map(Counter)                       \
    .map(lambda counts: {vocab_map_vk.value[token]: float(counts[token]) for token in counts}) \
    .map(lambda index_counts: SparseVector(vocab_size.value, index_counts))                 \
    .zipWithIndex().map(lambda x: [x[1], x[0]]).cache()

# Cluster the documents into three topics using LDA
ldaModel = LDA.train(term_document_matix, k=number_clusters)

#ZEND

paragraphs.title: View Data-Driven Topics
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

# Output topics. Each is a distribution over words (matching word count vectors)
print("Learned topics (as distributions over vocab of " + str(ldaModel.vocabSize())
      + " words):")

topics = ldaModel.topicsMatrix()
for topic in range(number_clusters):
    print("Topic " + str(topic) + ":")
    words = []
    for word in range(0, ldaModel.vocabSize()):
        #print(" " + str(topics[word][topic])) + "\t" + str(vocab_map_kv.value[word])
        words.append([topics[word][topic], vocab_map_kv.value[word]])
    
    words_sorted = sorted(words, key=lambda t: (-t[0]))
    #print words_sorted
    
    for i,topic_term in enumerate(words_sorted):
        if i >= 75 and i < 85:
            print "  " + str("%.6f" % topic_term[0]) + "\t" + str(topic_term[1])

paragraphs.text:
%md

What else can we do with these results?

Enhance Search: Categories (and enriched variables) can be fed into SOLR to enhance search Predictive Modeling: Categories, flags, and variables can be fed in to a predictive model (ie. What factors/variables influence what studies make it to Phase 4) Unsupervised Learning: Extract data-driven topics (text mining), used to uncover unknown patterns in textual data (can also be applied to structred data as clustering) Send to Hive: Write to Hive as an enriched table and for use with other operational systems. Write to HBase: Store the results in HBase for quick random-access / quick scanning & lookup of records.
